<p id="Par13" class="p">Water-equivalent mass change of glaciers can be expressed using elevation changes and glacier sensitivity as follows.
 <disp-formula id="Equ1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">1</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\frac{{\rm{\Delta }}M}{{\rm{\Delta }}t}=S\rho \frac{{\rm{\Delta }}h}{{\rm{\Delta }}t}=S(\frac{db}{dT}{\rm{\Delta }}T+\frac{db}{dP}{\rm{\Delta }}P)\,$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M2" display="block" class="math">
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">M</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">h</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mfrac class="mfrac">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        <mi class="mi">b</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfrac>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mo class="mo">+</mo>
      <mfrac class="mfrac">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        <mi class="mi">b</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        <mi class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </mfrac>
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
      <mi class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mspace width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41598_2017_14256_Article_Equ1.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where, 
 <italic class="italic">M</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">S</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">ρ</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">h</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">b</italic>, 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>, and 
 <italic class="italic">P</italic> are glacier mass, time, glacier area, density of snow or ice, glacier elevation, specific mass balance, temperature, and precipitation, respectively. 
 <italic class="italic">db</italic>/
 <italic class="italic">dt</italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">db</italic>/
 <italic class="italic">dP</italic> in eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ1" ref-type="" class="xref">1</xref>) indicate mass balance sensitivity to temperature (MBS) and precipitation, respectively, which are expressed as glacier responses to climate change. The spatial distribution of 
 <italic class="italic">ΔT</italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">ΔP</italic> are expressed as climate change.
</p>
